body:
The `StreamConsumerFactory` should be able to supply everything related to the stream i.e. messages and metadata. The `StreamConsumerFactory` provides `Consumers` and `MetadataProviders`. Consumers can be of 2 kinds viz. `StreamLevelConsumer` and `PartitionLevelConsumer`. `The StreamConsumerFactory` should be able to provide both a stream level consumer and a partition level consumer (as applicable to the stream). 
```
public interface StreamConsumerFactory {
  
  PartitionLevelConsumer createPartitionLevelConsumer(int partition);
  
  StreamLevelConsumer createStreamLevelConsumer();
  
  StreamMetadataProvider createStreamMetadataProvider();
 
  StreamMetadataProvider createPartitionMetadataProvider();
}
```
For example, we will now have a single `KafkaConsumerFactory`, which will provide a `KafkaPartitionLevelConsume` for low level consumption, and a `KafkaStreamLevelConsumer` for high level consumption. This PR introduces the concepts of 2 types of consumers supplied by a single stream factory. Code wise, there isn't any new logic or code, but simply movement of code which already performed those roles. `StreamLevelConsumer` was formerly `StreamProvider`, and `PartitionLevelConsumer` was formerly `StreamConsumer`.

**NOTE**
**Starting with this PR, for any users of High Level kafka stream, the StreamConsumerFactory will be expected in stream configs in the table config as** 
```
"stream.kafka.consumer.factory.class.name": "com.linkedin.pinot.core.realtime.impl.kafka.SimpleConsumerFactory"
``` 
**There are no hardcoded paths in the code anymore which will by default make the high level kafka stream work.**
